#include "Action_Memory.h"
#include <cstring>
/*!
* \brief
* Creates the ObjectManager per the specified values. Throws an exception if the construction
* fails. (Memory allocation problem)
*
* \param ObjectSize
* The size of the object to keep track of the memory of
*
* \param config
* Settings for the allocator, see ObjectAllocator.h for options
*/
ObjectAllocator::ObjectAllocator(size_t ObjectSize, const OAConfig &config) :
Config_(config), InterBlockSize_(0) {
//set the object size
Stats_.ObjectSize_ = ObjectSize;
//set the page size
Stats_.PageSize_ = Get_PageSize();
//if the memory allocated
if (!Config_.UseCPPMemManager_)
{
InterBlockSize_ = Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Stats_.ObjectSize_;
InterBlockSize_ += Config_.InterAlignSize_ + Config_.PadBytes_ * 2;
//allocate a page and add it to the allocator
Add_Page();
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* Destroys the ObjectManager (never throws)
*/
ObjectAllocator::~ObjectAllocator() {
//is the memory manager is in use
if (!Config_.UseCPPMemManager_)
{
//loop through the page list deleting all allocated memory for the pages
while (PageList_)
{
byte *temp = reinterpret_cast<byte *>(PageList_);
PageList_ = PageList_->Next;
delete[] temp;
}
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* Takes an object from the free list and returns it as allocated memory.
* Will through if there is a memory issue
*
* \param label
* A unique name given to the objects header
*
* \return
* returns a pointer to the allocated memory
*/
void *ObjectAllocator::Allocate(const char *label) {
void *rtn = nullptr; //pointer to return to the client
//if the memory manager is disabled, return an allocated void pointer
if (Config_.UseCPPMemManager_)
{
try
{
//allocate memory and keep track of allocations
++Stats_.Allocations_;
rtn = new byte[Stats_.ObjectSize_]();
}
catch (std::bad_alloc &)
{
--Stats_.Allocations_;
throw OAException(OAException::E_NO_MEMORY, "Object can't be allocated");
}
}
else
{
//if a new page needs to be allocated
if (Stats_.ObjectsInUse_ == Stats_.PagesInUse_ * Config_.ObjectsPerPage_)
Add_Page();
//remove the pointer from the free list
*reinterpret_cast<GenericObject **>(&rtn) = FreeList_;
FreeList_ = FreeList_->Next;
//update header data
Allocate_Header(Get_Header(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(rtn)), label);
//if debug is on, add the bytes
if (Config_.DebugOn_)
memset(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(rtn), ALLOCATED_PATTERN, Stats_.ObjectSize_);
}
//update objects in use and free objects
++Stats_.ObjectsInUse_;
--Stats_.FreeObjects_;
//check if its the most objects allocated at one time
if (Stats_.ObjectsInUse_ > Stats_.MostObjects_)
Stats_.MostObjects_ = Stats_.ObjectsInUse_;
//return the pointer
return rtn;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Frees memory allocated by the object allocator.Throws an exception if the the
* object can't be freed. (Invalid object)
*
* \param Object
* A unique name given to the objects header
*
* \return
* returns a pointer to the allocated memory
*/
void ObjectAllocator::Free(void *Object) {
//if the memory manager
if (Config_.UseCPPMemManager_)
{
//Track deallocations and free the memory
++Stats_.Deallocations_;
delete[] reinterpret_cast<byte *>(Object);
return;
}
//if the debug option is on, check for bounds, double freed and corruptions
if (Config_.DebugOn_)
{
//check if a block has already been freed throw an exception if so
if (Freed(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(Object)))
throw OAException(OAException::E_MULTIPLE_FREE,
"Object has already been freed or freed out of bounds");
//check if the object is out of bounds
if (OutOfBounds(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(Object)))
throw OAException(OAException::E_BAD_BOUNDARY, "Object out of range of its allocated memory");
//check if the pad bytes around the object is corrupted/overwritten. if so, throw an exception
if (Corrupted(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(Object)))
throw OAException(OAException::E_CORRUPTED_BLOCK,
"Pad bytes adjacent to object ptr has been overwritten");
//if debug is on, add the bytes
memset(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(Object), FREED_PATTERN, Stats_.ObjectSize_);
}
//add the object back to the free list
GenericObject *obj = reinterpret_cast<GenericObject *>(Object);
obj->Next = FreeList_;
FreeList_ = obj;
//free/update the header block attached to the data block
Free_Header(Get_Header(reinterpret_cast<byte *>(Object)));
//update states for freeing
--Stats_.ObjectsInUse_;
++Stats_.FreeObjects_;
++Stats_.Deallocations_;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Calls the function passed in on every object that is currently allocated within the page list
*
* \param fn
* function to run on all allocated blocks of data
*
* \return
* returns the number of blocks of data allocated within the allocator
*/
unsigned ObjectAllocator::DumpMemoryInUse(DUMPCALLBACK fn) const {
//if there are no pad bytes or debug is off, return zero
if (!Config_.DebugOn_ || Config_.PadBytes_)
return 0;
//pointer to the page list
GenericObject *run = PageList_;
//number of objects allocated
unsigned objs_allocated = 0;
//loop through all the pages
while (run)
{
//get the start of a page
byte *page = reinterpret_cast<byte *>(run);
//move to the first data block of data
page += sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
//loop through the page checking if each block is in use
for (size_t i = 0; i < Config_.ObjectsPerPage_; ++i, page += InterBlockSize_)
{
//check if the memory is in use
if (!Freed(page))
{
//print out the memory and add one to the allocated number
fn(page, Stats_.ObjectSize_);
++objs_allocated;
}
}
//move to the next page
run = run->Next;
}
//return the number of objects in use by the memory
return objs_allocated;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Calls the callback fn for each block that is potentially corrupted
*
* \param fn
* callback function for using on every block of memory that might be corrupted
*
* \return
* the number of objects corrupted
*/
unsigned ObjectAllocator::ValidatePages(VALIDATECALLBACK fn) const {
//if there are no pad bytes or debug is off, return zero
if (!Config_.DebugOn_ || !Config_.PadBytes_)
return 0;
//pointer to the page list
GenericObject *run = PageList_;
//number of objects corrupted
unsigned objs_corrupted = 0;
//loop through all the pages
while (run)
{
//get the start of a page
byte *page = reinterpret_cast<byte *>(run);
//move to the first data block of data
page += sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
//loop through the page checking if each block is corrupted
for (size_t i = 0; i < Config_.ObjectsPerPage_; ++i, page += InterBlockSize_)
{
//check if the pad bytes around the block corrupted
if (Corrupted(page))
{
//print out the memory and add one to the corrupted count
fn(page, Stats_.ObjectSize_);
++objs_corrupted;
}
}
//move to the next page
run = run->Next;
}
//return the number of objects corrupted
return objs_corrupted;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Frees all empty pages
*
* \return
* returns the number of pages freed
*/
unsigned ObjectAllocator::FreeEmptyPages() {
GenericObject *run = PageList_; //pointer to the page list
//number of objects corrupted
unsigned pages_freed = 0;
//loop through all the pages
while (run)
{
//get the start of a page
byte *page = reinterpret_cast<byte *>(run);
if (PageFree(page))
{
RemoveFreeListPage(page); //reorder the free list to not include the page about to free
RemoveNode(&PageList_, run); //remove the page from the page list
byte *temp = page;
run = run->Next;
delete[] temp;
//increase freed pages
--Stats_.PagesInUse_;
Stats_.FreeObjects_ -= Config_.ObjectsPerPage_;
++pages_freed;
}
else
{
//move to the next page
run = run->Next;
}
}
//return the number of objects corrupted
return pages_freed;
}

/*!
* \brief
* Helper function for updating the header block of an object during allocations
*
* \param header
* the first byte of the header block
*
* \param label
* the label to attach to the external header block
*/
void ObjectAllocator::Allocate_Header(byte *header, const char *label) {
//update allocations_
++Stats_.Allocations_;
//if basic, alloc # + flag byte
if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ == OAConfig::hbBasic)
{
//add one to the allocation count
*reinterpret_cast<unsigned *>(header) = Stats_.Allocations_;
//set the bool flag to true
*reinterpret_cast<bool *>(header + sizeof(unsigned)) = true;
}
//if extended, user-defined + use counter + alloc # + flag byte
else
if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ == OAConfig::hbExtended)
{
//add one to the re-use count
++*reinterpret_cast<short *>(header + Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_);
//add one to the allocation count
*reinterpret_cast<unsigned *>(header + Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_ +
sizeof(short)) = Stats_.Allocations_;
//set the bool flag to true
*reinterpret_cast<bool *>(header + Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_ + sizeof(short) +
sizeof(unsigned)) = true;
}
//if external, allocate obj
else
if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ == OAConfig::hbExternal)
{
//get a pointer size of memory from the page
MemBlockInfo **header_block = reinterpret_cast<MemBlockInfo **>(header);
try
{
//allocate the pointer
(*header_block) = new MemBlockInfo;
}
catch (std::bad_alloc &)
{
//throw if no memory
throw OAException(OAException::E_NO_MEMORY, "Unable to allocate external header");
}
//if there is a label to apply
if (label)
{
try
{
//allocate the char array
(*header_block)->label = new char[strlen(label) + 1]();
}
catch (std::bad_alloc &)
{
//throw of there is no memory
throw OAException(OAException::E_NO_MEMORY, "Unable to allocate external header label");
}
//copy the label into the headers label
strcpy((*header_block)->label, label);
}
//set the in use to in use
(*header_block)->in_use = true;
//set the allocation number
(*header_block)->alloc_num = Stats_.Allocations_;
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* Helper function for updating the header block of an object during freeing
*
* \param header
* the first byte of the header block
*/
void ObjectAllocator::Free_Header(byte *header) {
//if external, allocate obj
if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ == OAConfig::hbExternal)
{
//get pointer to memory
MemBlockInfo *head_ptr = *reinterpret_cast<MemBlockInfo **>(header);
//delete the label attached to the header
delete[] head_ptr->label;
head_ptr->label = nullptr;
//delete the header
delete head_ptr;
}
//set the extended header to zeros keeping the fist two bytes with the object
if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ == OAConfig::hbExtended)
{
memset(header, 0, Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_);
memset(header + Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_ + sizeof(short), 0, Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ - sizeof(short) - Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_);
}
//set the memory to zero if a block is present
else if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ != OAConfig::hbNone)
{
memset(header, 0, Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_);
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* given a header block, check if the data has been freed
*
* \param object
* the first byte of the object data
*
* \return
* return if the object passed in has been freed
*/
bool ObjectAllocator::Freed(byte *object) const {
if (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ != OAConfig::hbNone)
{
//check to see if the block is extended
size_t offset = (Config_.HBlockInfo_.type_ == OAConfig::hbExtended ? Config_.HBlockInfo_.additional_ + sizeof(short): 0);
//compare the header with an array of 0s
byte *arr = new byte[Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_]();
bool result = !memcmp(Get_Header(object) + offset, arr, Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ - offset);
delete[] arr;
return result;
}
//check if the object passed in is on the free list
GenericObject *run = FreeList_;
while (run)
{
//pointer to first element of a page
if (object == reinterpret_cast<byte *>(run))
return true;
//move to the next page
run = run->Next;
}
return false;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Calculates and returns page size
* \return
* returns the size of the page in bytes
*/
size_t ObjectAllocator::Get_PageSize() {
//check if alignment needs to be calculated
if (Config_.Alignment_ > 1)
{
//calculate the bytes needed for the left alignment
size_t front_bytes = sizeof(void *) + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
Config_.LeftAlignSize_ =
Config_.Alignment_ - (static_cast<unsigned>(front_bytes) % Config_.Alignment_);
//calculate the bytes needed for the inter block alignment
size_t inter_bytes = Stats_.ObjectSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_ * 2;
Config_.InterAlignSize_ =
Config_.Alignment_ - (static_cast<unsigned>(inter_bytes) % Config_.Alignment_);
}
//size of the page
size_t size = 0;
// next page pointer + left alignment block (only the first block has left alignment)
size = sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_;
// Each object has a header, left padding, the object itself, right padding
// (The left and right padding blocks are the same size)
size += Config_.ObjectsPerPage_ *
(Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_ + Stats_.ObjectSize_ + Config_.PadBytes_);
// All but the first block have an inter-block alignment block
size += (Config_.ObjectsPerPage_ - 1) * Config_.InterAlignSize_;
return size;
}
/*!
* \brief
* allocates the memory size of one page. will throw if page cant be allocated
* \return
* returns allocated pointer
*/
ObjectAllocator::byte *ObjectAllocator::Allocate_Page() {
try
{
//return allocated memory filled with UNALLOCATED_PATTERN value
return reinterpret_cast<byte *>(new byte[Stats_.PageSize_]());
}
catch (std::bad_alloc &)
{
throw OAException(OAException::E_NO_MEMORY, "Unable to allocate page");
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* Populates a page with all debug pattern bytes
* \param page
* the first byte of a page
*/
void ObjectAllocator::Populate_Page(byte *page) {
//set Null values for Page list pointer
memset(page, 0, sizeof(void *));
//set the alignment bytes for the left block
memset(page + sizeof(void *), ALIGN_PATTERN, Config_.LeftAlignSize_);
//sets header, padding, datam padding
auto Set_Block_Bytes = [&](byte *head_pos) {
//header
memset(head_pos, 0, Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_);
//padding
memset(head_pos + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_, PAD_PATTERN, Config_.PadBytes_);
//padding
memset(head_pos + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_ + Stats_.ObjectSize_,
PAD_PATTERN, Config_.PadBytes_);
return void(0);
};
//The total size of the inter block bytes minus the alignment
size_t InterBlockSizeIsh = InterBlockSize_ - Config_.InterAlignSize_;
//Run through the list setting the bytes of each inter block
for (size_t i = 0, offset = sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_;
i < Config_.ObjectsPerPage_; ++i, offset += InterBlockSizeIsh)
{
//alignment when i != 0
if (i)
{
memset(page + offset, ALIGN_PATTERN, Config_.InterAlignSize_);
offset += Config_.InterAlignSize_;
}
//offsets in relation to the start of the header
Set_Block_Bytes(page + offset);
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* allocates and adds a page to the front of the page list
*/
void ObjectAllocator::Add_Page() {
//checks if page count max has been reached
if (Config_.MaxPages_ && (Stats_.PagesInUse_ == Config_.MaxPages_))
throw OAException(OAException::E_NO_PAGES, "Max pages have been reached");
//allocate a new block of memory
byte *new_page = Allocate_Page();
//populate the page for debugging
if (Config_.DebugOn_)
{
//mem set the whole page with unallocated pattern
memset(new_page, UNALLOCATED_PATTERN, Stats_.PageSize_);
//populate the page with all the proper patterns
Populate_Page(new_page);
}
//update pages in use and Free objects
++Stats_.PagesInUse_;
Stats_.FreeObjects_ += Config_.ObjectsPerPage_;
//insert the new page into the from of the page list
GenericObject *front_bytes = reinterpret_cast<GenericObject *>(new_page);
front_bytes->Next = PageList_;
PageList_ = front_bytes;
//move to where the block of data would be
new_page +=
sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
//setup pointers for freed list
for (size_t i = 0; i < Config_.ObjectsPerPage_; ++i, new_page += InterBlockSize_)
{
reinterpret_cast<GenericObject *>((new_page))->Next = FreeList_;
FreeList_ = reinterpret_cast<GenericObject *>(new_page);
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* given a block of data, gets the header attached to that block
*
* \param object
* the first byte of the object that you want to get the header of
* \return
*/
ObjectAllocator::byte *ObjectAllocator::Get_Header(byte *object) const {
return object - Config_.PadBytes_ - Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_;
}
/*!
* \brief
* checks if a block of data is corrupted or not
*
* \param object
* the first byte of the object you want to check for corruption for
*
* \return
* returns true if the block is corrupted
*/
bool ObjectAllocator::Corrupted(byte *object) const {
try
{
//allocate a string to compare with the pad bytes on the left and right
const byte *comp_str = reinterpret_cast<byte *>(memset(new byte[Config_.PadBytes_ + 1](),
PAD_PATTERN, Config_.PadBytes_));
if (memcmp(comp_str, object + Stats_.ObjectSize_, Config_.PadBytes_) ||
memcmp(comp_str, object - Config_.PadBytes_, Config_.PadBytes_))
{
//return that the block has been corrupted
delete[] comp_str;
return true;
}
delete[] comp_str;
}
//throw if the comp string couldn't be allocated
catch (std::bad_alloc &)
{
throw OAException(OAException::E_NO_MEMORY,
"String for comparing pad bytes unable to be allocated");
}
//the memory is not corrupted
return false;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Checks if an object is out of bounds
*
* \param object
* the object to check
*
* \return
* returns true if the object passed in is out of bounds
*/
bool ObjectAllocator::OutOfBounds(byte *object) const {
//pointer to the head of the page list
GenericObject *run = PageList_;
size_t Block_Alignment =
sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
//go though all the pages
while (run)
{
//pointer to first element of a page
byte *page = reinterpret_cast<byte *>(run);
long long int difference = object - page;
//check if the object is within the page
if (difference >= 0 && difference < static_cast<long long int>(Stats_.PageSize_))
{
//check if the position of the object is a multiple of all the other objects
return (difference % (InterBlockSize_) != Block_Alignment);
}
//move to the next page
run = run->Next;
}
return false;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Checks if a page contains only elements within the free list
*
* \param page
* the first byte of the page
*
* \return
* returns true if the page is free
*/
bool ObjectAllocator::PageFree(byte *page) const {
//move to the first data block of data
page += sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
//loop through the page checking if each block is corrupted
for (size_t i = 0; i < Config_.ObjectsPerPage_; ++i, page += InterBlockSize_)
{
//check if the pad bytes around the block corrupted
if (!Freed(page))
return false;
}
return true;
}
/*!
* \brief
* Reorders the free list to not include the page passed in
*
* \param page
* the page to remove the free list from
*/
void ObjectAllocator::RemoveFreeListPage(byte *page) {
//move to where the block of data would be
page += sizeof(void *) + Config_.LeftAlignSize_ + Config_.HBlockInfo_.size_ + Config_.PadBytes_;
//setup pointers for freed list
for (size_t i = 0; i < Config_.ObjectsPerPage_; ++i, page += InterBlockSize_)
{
RemoveNode(&FreeList_, reinterpret_cast<GenericObject *>((page)));
}
}
/*!
* \brief
* removes a node from a list
*
* \param list
* the list you want to remove the node from
*
* \param node
* the node to remove
*/
void ObjectAllocator::RemoveNode(GenericObject **list, GenericObject *node)
{
GenericObject *hold = *list; //pointer holder for removed node
GenericObject *remove = *list; //pointer holder for removed node
//move to where the node is
while (remove != node && remove->Next)
{
hold = remove;
remove = remove->Next;
}
//to avoid issues with null
if (!remove) return;
if (remove == *list) //if its the front of the list
*list = remove->Next; //set new head
else
hold->Next = remove->Next; //move to next node
}

/*****************************************************************************/
#ifndef ACTION_MEMORY_H
#define ACTION_MEMORY_H
#include <string>
//! If not specified, the objects per page will be this
static const int DEFAULT_OBJECTS_PER_PAGE = 4;
//! If not specified, the max pages will be this
static const int DEFAULT_MAX_PAGES = 3;
/*!
Exception class
*/
class OAException
{
public:
/*!
Possible exception codes
*/
enum OA_EXCEPTION
{
E_NO_MEMORY, //!< out of physical memory (operator new fails)
E_NO_PAGES, //!< out of logical memory (max pages has been reached)
E_BAD_BOUNDARY, //!< block address is on a page, but not on any block-boundary
E_MULTIPLE_FREE, //!< block has already been freed
E_CORRUPTED_BLOCK //!< block has been corrupted (pad bytes have been overwritten)
};
/*!
Constructor
\param ErrCode
One of the 5 error codes listed above
\param Message
A message returned by the what method.
*/
OAException(OA_EXCEPTION ErrCode, const std::string& Message) : error_code_(ErrCode), message_(Message) {};
/*!
Destructor
*/
virtual ~OAException() {
}
/*!
Retrieves the error code
\return
One of the 5 error codes.
*/
OA_EXCEPTION code() const {
return error_code_;
}
/*!
Retrieves a human-readable string regarding the error.
\return
The NUL-terminated string representing the error.
*/
virtual const char *what() const {
return message_.c_str();
}
private:
OA_EXCEPTION error_code_; //!< The error code (one of the 5)
std::string message_; //!< The formatted string for the user.
};
/*!
ObjectAllocator configuration parameters
*/
struct OAConfig
{
static const size_t BASIC_HEADER_SIZE = sizeof(unsigned) + 1; //!< allocation number + flags
static const size_t EXTERNAL_HEADER_SIZE = sizeof(void*); //!< just a pointer
/*!
The different types of header blocks
*/
enum HBLOCK_TYPE{hbNone, hbBasic, hbExtended, hbExternal};
/*!
POD that stores the information related to the header blocks.
*/
struct HeaderBlockInfo
{
HBLOCK_TYPE type_; //!< Which of the 4 header types to use?
size_t size_; //!< The size of this header
size_t additional_; //!< How many user-defined additional bytes
/*!
Constructor
\param type
The kind of header blocks in use.
\param additional
The number of user-defined additional bytes required.
*/
HeaderBlockInfo(HBLOCK_TYPE type = hbNone, unsigned additional = 0) : type_(type), size_(0), additional_(additional)
{
if (type_ == hbBasic)
size_ = BASIC_HEADER_SIZE;
else if (type_ == hbExtended) // alloc # + use counter + flag byte + user-defined
size_ = sizeof(unsigned int) + sizeof(unsigned short) + sizeof(char) + additional_;
else if (type_ == hbExternal)
size_ = EXTERNAL_HEADER_SIZE;
};
};

}

// Throws an exception if the object can't be allocated. (Memory allocation problem)
void *Allocate(const char *label = 0);

// Throws an exception if the the object can't be freed. (Invalid object)
void Free(void *Object);
// Calls the callback fn for each block still in use
unsigned DumpMemoryInUse(DUMPCALLBACK fn) const;

unsigned ValidatePages(VALIDATECALLBACK fn) const;
// Frees all empty pages (extra credit)
unsigned FreeEmptyPages();
// Returns true if FreeEmptyPages and alignments are implemented
static bool ImplementedExtraCredit();
// Testing/Debugging/Statistic methods
void SetDebugState(bool State); // true=enable, false=disable

OAConfig GetConfig() const; // returns the configuration parameters
OAStats GetStats() const; // returns the statistics for the allocator
// Prevent copy construction and assignment
ObjectAllocator(const ObjectAllocator &oa) = delete; //!< Do not implement!
ObjectAllocator &operator=(const ObjectAllocator &oa) = delete; //!< Do not implement!
private:
typedef unsigned char byte; //!< byte typedef for understanding code better
// Some "suggested" members (only a suggestion!)
GenericObject *PageList_ = { 0 }; //!< the beginning of the list of pages

void ActionParser::Parse(std::string Filename)
{
std::ifstream infile(Filename);
if (infile.is_open())
PreProccess(infile);
}
void ActionParser::PreProccess(std::ifstream &infile)
{
std::string line;
auto GetNextChar = [](std::string str, size_t &index){
while (isspace(str[index])) ++index;
};
while (!infile.eof())
{
size_t index = 0;
std::getline(infile, line);
GetNextChar(line, index);
if (line[index] == '@')
{
//clear the old group name and set the new one
currentActionGroup_ = std::string(line.begin() + ++index, line.end());
std::transform(currentActionGroup_.begin(), currentActionGroup_.end(),
currentActionGroup_.begin(), ::toupper);
}
else if (line[index] == '$')
{
GetNextChar(line, index); //get the first char of the name
int tempIndex = ++index;
//get the end of the word
while (!isspace(line[index]) && line[index] != '=') ++index;
std::string name(line.begin() + tempIndex, line.begin() + index); //get the action name
std::transform(name.begin(), name.end(), name.begin(), ::toupper);
while (line[index] != '=') ++index;
tempIndex = ++index;
while (line[index] != ';') ++index;
std::string expression(line.begin() + tempIndex, line.begin() + index);
ActionData_[currentActionGroup_][name] = expression;
}
}
infile.clear(); // clear fail and eof bits
infile.seekg(0, std::ios::beg); // back to the start
}

bool ActionTree::Evaluate(TreeNode *tree) const
{
if (tree->type_ == TreeNode::ANDOP || tree->type_ == TreeNode::OROP)
return tree->operator_(Evaluate(tree->left_), Evaluate(tree->right_));
return tree->input_();
}

void ActionTree::GetToken()
{
currToken_.clear(); //clear the token
//go to the next non-whitespace char
while (isspace(expression_[currPos_])) ++currPos_;
currToken_.push_back(expression_[currPos_++]);
//check if we got an operator
if (IsOperator(currToken_))
return;
//get the rest of the input hash and return
while (IsIdentifier(expression_[currPos_]))
currToken_.push_back(expression_[currPos_++]);
//uppercase everything
std::transform(currToken_.begin(), currToken_.end(), currToken_.begin(), ::toupper);
}
void ActionTree::CheckOr(TreeNode *&tree) // |
{
CheckAnd(tree);
while (currToken_ == "|")
{
auto temp = new TreeNode(nullptr, nullptr, TreeNode::OROP, [](bool L,bool R) { return L | R; });
temp->left_ = tree;
tree = temp;
GetToken();
CheckAnd(tree->right_);
}
}
void ActionTree::CheckAnd(TreeNode *&tree) // &
{
CheckNot(tree);
while (currToken_ == "&")
{
auto temp = new TreeNode(nullptr, nullptr, TreeNode::ANDOP, [](bool L,bool R) { return L & R; });
temp->left_ = tree;
tree = temp;
GetToken();
CheckNot(tree->right_);
}
}
void ActionTree::CheckNot(TreeNode *&tree) // !
{
//go to the end of all the not(s) and set the value there
if (currToken_ == "!")
{
GetToken();
CheckRest(tree);
std::function<bool()> temp = tree->input_;
tree->input_ = [temp](){return !temp();};
}
else
CheckRest(tree);
}
void ActionTree::CheckRest(TreeNode *&tree) // ( or input
{
if (currToken_ == "(")
{
GetToken();
CheckOr(tree);
}
//check if an action is within the preprocessed map
auto NestedActionCheck = ActionParser::ActionData_[ActionManager::CurrectActionGroup()].find(currToken_);
if (NestedActionCheck != ActionParser::ActionData_[ActionManager::CurrectActionGroup()].end())
{
//maybe move this within the lambda as a static member
//play around with this. Pointers might be an issue here. Or its very expensive
tree = new TreeNode(nullptr, nullptr, TreeNode::INPUT, [=]() {
ActionTree nested_tree;
nested_tree.Generate(NestedActionCheck->second);
return nested_tree.EvaluateTree();});
}
//TODO: put callback to input system here (check if key is within the action system)
else if(IsInput(currToken_))
tree = new TreeNode(nullptr, nullptr, TreeNode::INPUT, []() {return true; });
GetToken();
}
bool ActionTree::IsOperator(std::string token)
{
return (token == "|" || token == "&" || token == "!" || token == "(");
}
bool ActionTree::IsIdentifier(char token)
{
return (token >= 'a' && token <= 'z') || (token >= 'A' && token <= 'Z') || token == '_';
}
bool ActionTree::IsInput(std::string token)
{
//index into the map that has the look up keys
return token != ")" && !IsOperator(token);
}
void ActionTree::FreeTree(TreeNode *tree)
{
if (!tree)
return;
FreeTree(tree->left_);
FreeTree(tree->right_);
FreeNode(tree);
}
void ActionTree::FreeNode(TreeNode *node)
{
delete node;
}

void ActionManager::Import(std::string Filename)
{
ActionParser::Parse(Filename);
auto groupItter = ActionParser::ActionData_.begin();
while (groupItter != ActionParser::ActionData_.end())
{
//loop through each action within a group generating their ActionTree's
auto actionItter = groupItter->second.begin();
while (actionItter != groupItter->second.end())
{
actionManager_[groupItter->first][actionItter->first].Generate(actionItter->second);
++actionItter;
}
++groupItter;
}
}
void ActionManager::Reimport(std::string Filename)
{
actionManager_.clear();
Import(Filename);
}
